data.title: Love at Large
data.meta_description: Love at Large (1990) starring Tom Berenger, Elizabeth Perkins, Anne Archer and directed by Alan Rudolph.
data.text:
Nitrate OnlineDan Lybarger

As with a lot of Rudolph films, this one seems a little too pleased with its quirkiness.

Chicago Sun-TimesRoger Ebert

Here is a movie that looks like a parody, sounds like a parody and plays like a parody, but isn't a parody -- because the genre it's making fun of doesn't exist.

IONCINEMA.comNicholas Bell

Deliberately strange, to the degree where Love at Large refreshingly defies easy categorization, Rudolph's bizarre universe feels innovative even as it leads to an expected finale.
